# UI/UX Design Guidelines

## Design Principles
- Clean, modern, and professional interface
- Intuitive navigation and controls
- Responsive design for all screen sizes
- Accessibility-first approach
- Consistent visual language

## Color Scheme
- Primary: Professional monochrome with one acsent color
- Secondary: Accent colors for actions and status
- Success: Green for connected states
- Warning: Orange for connection issues
- Error: Red for critical errors
- Background: Light/dark theme support

## Typography
- Sans-serif fonts for readability
- Clear hierarchy with proper font weights
- Adequate contrast ratios (WCAG compliant)
- Responsive font sizing
- Consistent spacing and line heights

## Layout Structure
- Header: Connection status and controls
- Sidebar: Connection list and settings
- Main area: Remote desktop display
- Footer: Status information and quick actions
- Modal dialogs for configuration

## Connection Interface
- Connection wizard for new connections
- Quick connect for saved profiles
- Connection status indicators
- Disconnect/reconnect controls
- Connection quality metrics

## Remote Desktop Display
- Full-screen mode support
- Zoom and pan controls
- Multi-monitor switching
- Performance indicators
- Connection quality overlay

## Controls and Interactions
- Keyboard shortcuts for common actions
- Context menus for right-click
- Drag and drop for file transfer
- Touch gestures for mobile
- Voice commands (future enhancement)

## Responsive Design
- Mobile-first approach
- Adaptive layouts for different screen sizes
- Touch-friendly controls on mobile
- Landscape and portrait orientation support
- Tablet-optimized interface

## Accessibility Features
- Screen reader compatibility
- Keyboard navigation support
- High contrast mode
- Font size adjustment
- Color blind friendly design

## Loading States
- Skeleton screens for initial load
- Progress indicators for connections
- Smooth transitions between states
- Error states with clear messaging
- Offline mode indicators 